drivers_and_causes:
Rapid increases in SST due to the poleward movement of tropical water masses coincident with marine heatwaves; seasonal tropical lows and cyclonic weather. Sea-level rise and fluctuations linked to Indian Ocean Dipole. Aquaculture (e.g., pearling); tourism; oil and gas drilling; seismic surveys; salt works; 
water and resource abstraction; targeted recreational fishing (e.g., spangled emperor). Discharge of polluting substances from commercial shipping and recreational boating; 
seasonal (March to November) peaks in tourist numbers.
